<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>OSINT Technical Report</title>
  <style>
    body { font-family: Arial, sans-serif; margin: 40px; }
    h1, h2, h3 { color: #333; }
    h4 { color: #555; }
    .header { border-bottom: 2px solid #333; padding-bottom: 10px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
    .section { margin-bottom: 30px; }
    .data-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 15px 0; }
    .data-table th, .data-table td { border: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 8px; text-align: left; }
    .data-table th { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
    .finding { background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; margin: 10px 0; border-left: 4px solid #ffc107; }
    .evidence { background: #d1ecf1; padding: 10px; margin: 10px 0; border-left: 4px solid #0dcaf0; }
    .metadata { font-size: 0.9em; color: #666; }
    pre { background: #f8f9fa; padding: 15px; overflow-x: auto; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="header">
    <h1>OSINT Technical Report</h1>
    <div class="metadata">
      <p>Generated on: <%= Time.now.strftime('%B %d, %Y at %H:%M') %></p>
      <p>Report Type: Technical Analysis</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Research Overview</h2>
    <p>This technical report provides detailed findings from the OSINT research operation. The analysis includes technical data, evidence, and methodologies used during the investigation.</p>
    
    <% if research_data && research_data['target'] %>
      <h3>Target Information</h3>
      <table class="data-table">
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Value</th>
        </tr>
        <% research_data['target'].each do |key, value| %>
          <tr>
            <td><%= key.capitalize %></td>
            <td><%= value %></td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
      </table>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Technical Findings</h2>
    <% if research_data && research_data['technical_findings'] %>
      <% research_data['technical_findings'].each_with_index do |finding, index| %>
        <div class="finding">
          <h4>Finding #<%= index + 1 %>: <%= finding['title'] %></h4>
          <p><%= finding['description'] %></p>
          
          <% if finding['evidence'] %>
            <div class="evidence">
              <h5>Evidence:</h5>
              <pre><%= finding['evidence'] %></pre>
            </div>
          <% end %>
          
          <% if finding['severity'] %>
            <p><strong>Severity:</strong> <%= finding['severity'] %></p>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      <% end %>
    <% else %>
      <p>No technical findings were provided in the research data.</p>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Data Sources</h2>
    <% if research_data && research_data['sources'] %>
      <ul>
        <% research_data['sources'].each do |source| %>
          <li><%= source %></li>
        <% end %>
      </ul>
    <% else %>
      <p>No data sources were specified in the research data.</p>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Methodology</h2>
    <p>The research was conducted using the following technical approaches:</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Reconnaissance:</strong> Initial information gathering through passive means</li>
      <li><strong>Enumeration:</strong> Active scanning and enumeration of targets</li>
      <li><strong>Analysis:</strong> Correlation and analysis of collected data</li>
      <li><strong>Verification:</strong> Validation of findings through multiple sources</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Limitations</h2>
    <p>This research has the following limitations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Data is based on publicly available information only</li>
      <li>Information may be outdated or inaccurate</li>
      <li>Some sources may have restricted access</li>
      <li>Technical limitations of collection methods</li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</body>
</html>